FBIS4-57710 "drlat100_o_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-100 Daily Report 24 May 1994 Colombia Authorities Link 22 May Attack to Medellin Cartel Authorities Link 22 May Attack to Medellin Cartel PA2405044194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 24 May 94 PA2405044194 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Spanish BFN [Report by Alvaro Ayala from the "24 Hours" Newscast] [Text] Although authorities have not ruled out that the Guerrilla Coordinating Board could have exploded a car bomb [on 22 May] that killed six men in uniform and injured nine other people, the strongest theory is that this was a strike by the terrorist wing of the Medellin Cartel. An official report states that after it was announced that Germany's Eintracht soccer team would play at the Atanasio Girardot Stadium intelligence organizations traced several telephone threats against this team, because the government of that country refused to grant asylum to the family of the late capo Pablo Escobar Gaviria [Begin National Police Director General Octavio Vargas Silva recording, identified by caption] There were several calls. We are analyzing this and other information at our disposal and we will, in due time, issue a complete report on what really happened. [end recording] The police in Antioquia Department were placed on maximum alert following the terrorist attack.
